modules.description: Handles parsing and rendering of KiCAD schematic files into a painter context. It processes schematic lines and library definitions to build an in-memory representation, which is then output as an image using the provided painter module. Useful for generating visualizations or exports of KiCAD schematics in custom formats.

This module defines core data types and transformation structures used in KiCAD schematic rendering, including coordinates, sizes, orientations, text styles, and colors. It provides interfaces for painter modules that handle schematic elements like components and annotations. Concrete use cases include defining graphical properties for KiCAD symbols and managing text formatting in schematics.

This module provides functions for parsing KiCAD schematic files and rendering them into visual outputs using a painter context. It works with data structures representing schematic elements such as components, annotations, coordinates, text styles, and colors. Concrete use cases include generating images of KiCAD schematics and exporting them in custom formats.
